"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The `metric` parameter in the `DBSCAN` class expects a callable that takes two arrays from X as input and returns a value indicating the distance between them. However, the `get_point_distance` function returns a 2D array (result of `euclidean_distances`), not a single distance value. This will cause an error when `DBSCAN` tries to use this function.\",\n  \"patch\": \"26c26\\n<    return euclidean_distances([p1.to_list()], [p2.to_list()])\\n---\\n>    return euclidean_distances([p1.to_list()], [p2.to_list()])[0][0]\"\n}"